SYPHILIS - RUSSIA: (BASHKORTOSTAN)
**********************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 6 Jan 2022 18:19 YEKT
Source: UfaTime [in Russian, machine trans., edited]
https://ufatime.ru/news/2022/01/06/v-bashkirii-nazvali-kolichestvo-detej-zarazivshihsya-sifilisom-v-2021-godu/


Experts have released data on the incidence of syphilis among residents of Bashkiria [Bashkortostan] for January-November 2021. The statistics were published by Roszdravnadzor [Federal Service for Surveillance in Healthcare]. Over 11 months of last year [2021], 200 cases of the disease were recorded in the Republic. Compared to the same period in 2020, the incidence decreased by 8%, or 12 cases.

Also in January-November [2021], experts discovered syphilis in 2 children under 14 years of age. In 2020, this diagnosis was made in one child.

The incidence rate of sexually transmitted diseases in Bashkiria is 4.94 per 100 000 population. In the Volga Federal District, the region most affected by syphilis is the Saratov region -- 16.95 per 100 000 inhabitants.

Note that syphilis is a sexually transmitted disease. There are times when infection occurs in a household way: through dishes, towels, toothbrushes, and so on.

[Byline: Regina Nurtdinova]

